message.content:
cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with transducers and automata.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses a new construction method for decomposing transducers, which involves a lexicographic ordering of computations.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the decomposition of rational relations, which can be seen as a logical problem.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the construction method used for the decomposition.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the improvement in complexity of the construction method compared to the original one.
